At least seven people died Monday and hundreds were injured when a severe tremor shook Turkey in the same region where more than 15,000 people were killed in a huge earthquake less than a month ago.
The quake virtually leveled parts of Izmit, 60 miles east of Istanbul, and other towns in western Turkey.
In Golcuk, a town on the Sea of Marmara that was one of the hardest hit by the Aug. 17 quake Tuesday's tremor sent people racing away from blocks of already weakened buildings.
